Freddie Blom has turned a whopping 115 years old. CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town man has lived to tell a wealth of tales. Freddie Blom has turned a whopping 115 years old. He was honoured at a special party to mark this milestone birthday. Surrounded by 115 other senior guests and family, Oupa Blom as he’s fondly known was celebrated at a party hosted by the Delft Senior forum. Oupa Blom hails from Adelaide in the Eastern Cape and was born in a leap year way back in 1904. So what is his secret to longevity? "The secret? There’s only one man who has the secret. I don’t have it. Only God has the secret. "From a young age, I’d followed the scripture ‘honour thy mother and thy father and your days will be lengthened.”